OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FAs millions of people prepare to vote
OL,8,Fin local elections, ITV News
OL,9,FInvestigations Editor Daniel Hewitt
OL,10,Fhas been finding out how the cost of
OL,11,Fliving remains a major concern across
OL,12,Fthe country
OL,14,FDavina doesn't want to be calling her
OL,15,F90-year-old mum to ask for help, but
OL,16,Fwhat choice does she have?
OL,18,FHer partner, Michael, was made
OL,19,Fredundant from his job as a chef, and
OL,20,Fhis Universal Credit application was
OL,21,Fdelayed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FDavina's wage as a supermarket cleaner
OL,8,Falways helped cover the bills, but
OL,9,Fcouldn't cover them alone. There was
OL,10,Fsimply not enough in her bank account.
OL,12,FHer mum lent her money to pay the rent
OL,13,Fand keep the lights on, but not every
OL,14,Fcost could be covered, and so debt
OL,15,Fstarted to build.
OL,17,FIt wasn't always like this.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FI first met Michael and Davina three
OL,8,Fand a half years ago. I went to North
OL,9,FShields in the north east of England
OL,10,Fto produce a series of reports on the
OL,11,Fcost of living crisis, with energy
OL,12,Fbills skyrocketing and inflation
OL,13,Frising.
OL,15,FMichael was doing ok, but not everyone
OL,16,Faround him was.
OL,18,FSo in his spare time, he was making
OL,19,Ffood for his neighbours and friends
OL,20,Fwho were struggling to afford regular
OL,21,Fmeals.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FI went with him as he dropped off
OL,8,Ftrays of sandwiches and savoury scones
OL,9,Fto his friend John, who lived alone.
OL,11,FThat was in 2022. When I arrived at
OL,12,Fhis house this week, Michael greeted
OL,13,Fme with a familiar warm, welcoming
OL,14,Fsmile, but it was quickly clear that
OL,15,Fthe struggle had also arrived at his
OL,16,Fdoor.
OL,18,FThe community kitchen he worked in had
OL,19,Fits funding cut, and last year,
OL,20,FMichael was let go.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,F"I got a little bit of redundancy
OL,8,Fmoney, but not a lot. It came to the
OL,9,Fpoint where I couldn't pay my rent, it
OL,10,Fwas just as simple as that," he told
OL,11,Fme.
OL,13,F"If I am honest, we were in dire
OL,14,Fstraits, and that just knocked me into
OL,15,Fa depression, really. I'm on
OL,16,Fantidepressant tablets. I was used to
OL,17,Fworking every day."
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@\O]uD@AOUyD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FWhen I asked about the meals he used
OL,8,Fto make for others, he said,
OL,9,Fregretfully, that he doesn't have the
OL,10,Fmoney to do it now.
OL,12,FFor five months, they tried and failed
OL,13,Fto survive on Davina's #700 cleaning
OL,14,Fwage.
OL,16,FThen his Universal Credit finally came
OL,17,Fthrough late last year, with a
OL,18,Fbackdated payment for the months he
OL,19,Fshould have been receiving it. I asked
OL,20,Fhow he's doing now.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,F"We're managing, yeah. I mean, we're
OL,8,Fnot uncomfortable," he said.
OL,10,F"It's not as if we've got any money
OL,11,Fleft at the end of the week, but
OL,12,Fthat's not the point. We don't need
OL,13,Fany money at the end of the week.
OL,14,FWe're getting by with what we have."
OL,16,FI have known Michael for a few years
OL,17,Fnow, and I know from our conversations
OL,18,Fthat he is a proud man who would
OL,19,Flikely put on a brave face rather than
OL,20,Ftell me how bad things really are.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FWhen I put that to him, he said:
OL,8,F"Well, you don't go into everything.
OL,9,FIt's private."
OL,11,FIn the kitchen, Davina tells me things
OL,12,Fare "very, very hard".
OL,14,F"I've had to borrow off my mum," she
OL,15,Fsaid. "I mean, my mom doesn't work
OL,16,Fanymore. She's nearly 90. It's just
OL,17,Fthe cost of being alive, really."
OL,19,FMichael lives on the Meadow Well
OL,20,Festate, one of the most deprived areas
OL,21,Fof the country.
OL,26,@pD@AOUqD@NO]vD@AOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FWhen I first came here in the autumn
OL,8,Fof 2022, people lived under a
OL,9,FConservative government, in a cost of
OL,10,Fliving crisis, with a prime minister
OL,11,Fin political peril, a sluggish economy
OL,12,Fand the price of everything rising.
OL,14,FToday they have a Labour government,
OL,15,Fin a cost of living crisis, with a
OL,16,Fprime minister in political peril, a
OL,17,Fsluggish economy and the price of
OL,18,Feverything rising.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FI wanted to ask the same people I met
OL,8,Fback then if things have got any
OL,9,Fbetter.
OL,11,FBack then, Liz Wright let us into her
OL,12,Flife at her lowest moment. She was in
OL,13,Fher 60s, working two jobs to get by,
OL,14,Fbut then came an energy bill twice as
OL,15,Fmuch as the last one, which she had no
OL,16,Fidea how to pay.
OL,18,F"I'm really worried," she said in 2022.
OL,26,@zD@AOUzD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,F"I have the heating on for an hour a
OL,8,Fday, I barely use my cooker, I don't
OL,9,Fuse my toaster ` it's a luxury to have
OL,10,Fa piece of toast. I'm going to have to
OL,11,Fexplain that I've got no money, and I
OL,12,Fcan't live."
OL,14,FThree and a half years later, I met
OL,15,FLiz at a different house.
OL,17,FShe has downsized from a three-bedroom
OL,18,Fhouse to a one-bedroom bungalow, and
OL,19,Fretired, cashing in a small pension,
OL,20,Fwhile getting a little help from her
OL,21,Ffamily.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FShe said she is no longer in debt and
OL,8,Fis in a much better place than she
OL,9,Fwas, but does worry about rising costs.
OL,11,F"I went shopping the other day, not
OL,12,Ffor my freezer, just to last me the
OL,13,Fweek and it cost us #39," she said.
OL,14,F"And I was like, 'what you added on to
OL,15,Fme bill?'. I said, 'give us a look'.
OL,17,F"Everybody's screaming where are they
OL,18,Fgoing to get the money from."
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@AOUzD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,8,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,9,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,10,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,12,FShe said "nothing has changed" in the
OL,13,Flast three and a half years to help
OL,14,Fher or people like her, but has some
OL,15,Fsympathy with the government having to
OL,16,Fdeal with events beyond their control.
OL,18,FShe added: "It's unrest, isn't it?
OL,19,FIt's a scary thing - he's a nutter."
OL,21,FWho is? I ask.
OL,26,@zD@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,F"Trump," she replied, blaming the war
OL,8,Fin Iran for pushing up fuel prices.
OL,9,F"He's not right. How are people going
OL,10,Fto get to work if they can't get any
OL,11,Fpetrol?"
OL,13,FHowever, energy prices are lower now
OL,14,Fthan they were when we were last in
OL,15,FNorth Shields.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FBack then, Neil owned four butcher
OL,8,Fshops in the area that his nan opened
OL,9,Fin the 1950s, but the energy bill for
OL,10,Fhis businesses had more than doubled,
OL,11,Fand not enough money was coming in to
OL,12,Fpay them.
OL,14,FHe predicted it was unsustainable.
OL,16,F"I think it's the end of an era," he
OL,17,Fsaid, and his prediction came to pass.
OL,18,FIn 2023, he shut down all of his
OL,19,Fbusinesses.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FI met him outside the shop on the
OL,8,FMeadow Well, shutters down, letters
OL,9,Ffrom the sign slowly falling off.
OL,11,F"Oh, it was heartbreaking," he said.
OL,13,F"It was like a bereavement. It had
OL,14,Fbeen my whole life for 40 years, and
OL,15,Fthat was just working here. Before
OL,16,Fthat, I was a child working here."
OL,18,FNeil missed it desperately at first,
OL,19,Fnot knowing what to do with himself,
OL,20,Fbut now feels "relieved" to be out.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@[O]uD@AOUxD@bO]|D@OOU|D@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,F"Anybody who wants to start a small
OL,8,Fbusiness now must be crazy with what's
OL,9,Fhappened in recent years.
OL,11,F"The first increase in the minimum
OL,12,Fwage would have cost us over #600 a
OL,13,Fweek. Then you find out they've
OL,14,Fadjusted the national insurance.
OL,16,F"I'm quite happy now that I haven't
OL,17,Fgot the stress of employing people and
OL,18,Frunning the business."
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUxD@AOUzD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FThe energy crisis cost Neil his shops,
OL,8,Fbut for so many, the cost of living
OL,9,Fcrisis I came here to cover in 2022
OL,10,Fhas not ended.
OL,12,FEmma runs a local social club, where
OL,13,Fmidweek bingo nights and weekend
OL,14,Ftribute bands help keep the doors open.
OL,16,FShe is a working mum with a mortgage
OL,17,Fand mouths to feed, and she sometimes
OL,18,Fwonders when the struggle will end.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31419
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,F"Rent and mortgage, council tax, the
OL,8,Fcost of food and essentials is really,
OL,9,Freally bad now," Emma said.
OL,11,F"There's nothing you can see that
OL,12,Fmakes you think it's going in the
OL,13,Fright direction. I think everything's
OL,14,Fjust sort of stagnant at the minute
OL,15,Fand nothing seems to be going for the
OL,16,Fbetter. I wish it would be different,
OL,17,Fbut it's not."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@PO]sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31420
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777651869
OL,3,CFrom always working to anti-
OL,4,Cdepressants: A never ending cost of
OL,5,Cliving crisis
OL,7,FWhat I found when I was last here was
OL,8,Ffear. The shock of such severe price
OL,9,Frises, particularly for energy and
OL,10,Ffood, left people worrying how they
OL,11,Fwould pay for it.
